				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: fear kite training <a name="6420"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 17 03 2:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For AFK training I have started using PoK.  I go to a corner, or climb a tree and play.
<br />

<br />
On Fearkiting you are best off to take em 1 at a time, though if you get an add just let it yo yo away and back while you kill the other.
<br />

<br />
For fearkiting at 26.  I am gonna suggest Lake of Ill Omen.
<br />

<br />
There are a couple of good spots there, both by the shore of the lake.  
<br />

<br />
Between the sarnak fort and the goblin-ruins-close-to-the-river, there is a stretch of shoreline.  There is a pass thru the mountain that parallells the shoreline.  There is a goblin tower just thru the pass.  Basically this is the southern shore of the lake.  At that pass many sarnaks, goblins, skeletons, and grimalkins pass by.  Pull to the shoreline, snare 1 and fear, he will run along the shoreline with little chance of adds.  If your target gets to the end of the mountain without dying, selos back to the pull point and wait for him, to avoid adds.
<br />

<br />
The other spot is at the pillars on the west side of the lake.  Lots of tasty morsels in the field there and good pathing if you start south of the pillars, they run northward and should die well before the goblin ruins at the north end of that beach.  Once again if they go to far, run back to start and begin again.
<br />

<br />
When I did this I would sometimes twist instruments with chords, denons, chains, fear.  Generally though I used weapons and chains, fear, denons, swapping hymn for denons if I took some hits.
<br />

<br />
Good Luck and may I suggest picking up a rogue buddy for your fearkite, XPs FLY.  I once had a group of 3 rogues and me fearkiting, they were worried about the healing but learned it was not a problem.  XP bar was SWEEEET.  
<br />

<br />
I macroed the lyrics to &quot;Baby Got Back&quot;</span></td>
